issue.title: Improves error message when input names are wrong

repository.name: sklearn-onnx
repository.description: Convert scikit-learn models and pipelines to ONNX

body:
There are two issues with your pipelines. The first one is the input names. ``initial_type = [('strfeat', StringTensorType([None, 2]))]``. The converter expects to see the same column names defined as inputs. Si it should be 

```
initial_type = [('KLIENTORGNR', StringTensorType([None, 1])),
                  ('LEVORGNR', StringTensorType([None, 1])),
                  ('clean_FAKTURALINJETEKST', StringTensorType([None, 1]))]
```

I create a PR to make the error message more explicit in that case. The second issue is there is no converter for MultiOutputClassifier. I'll create one this week.

Please Inform me when you're done with this 
Thanks

issue.title: Add converters for MultiOutputRegressor and MultiOutputClassifier

repository.name: sklearn-onnx
repository.description: Convert scikit-learn models and pipelines to ONNX

issue.body:
This PR introduces converters for MultiOutputRegressor and MultiOutputClassifier. It also fixes unexpected errors when implementing a custom converter such as mentioned in issues #711 and #712. It also refactors the file _topology.py to introduce logging. They can be enables by running the following instructions before converting a model:

```
import logging
logger = logging.getLogger('skl2onnx')
logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)
logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)
```

body:
That should be the same issue as in #716, `X_train['...']` is a dataframe not an array. You should use `X_train['...'].values`. You should also update the indices here:

```
input_name1 = sess.get_inputs()[0].name
input_name2 = sess.get_inputs()[0].name  --> [1]
input_name3 = sess.get_inputs()[0].name  --> [2]
```
